<rss xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" version="2.0"><channel><title>MariaDB Knowledge Base Comments for: How to configure ColumnStore job log?</title><link>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/how-to-configure-columnstore-job-log/+comments/feed/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://mariadb.com/kb/en/how-to-configure-columnstore-job-log/+comments/feed/" rel="self"></atom:link><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 10 Mar 2023 01:16:27 +0000</lastBuildDate><item><title>Re: How to configure ColumnStore job log?</title><link>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/how-to-configure-columnstore-job-log/+comments/4702</link><description>&lt;p&gt;As far as I know it's safe to add this to general columnstore logrotate conf file in /etc/logrotate.d/columnstore&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;/usr/local/mariadb/columnstore/data/bulk/log/* 
{   
    missingok    
    rotate 3    
    daily    
    maxage 3
}&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;/tmp/columnstore_tmp_files/* 
{   
    missingok    
    rotate 3    
    daily    
    maxage 3
}&lt;/p&gt;
</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">John Malcolm</dc:creator><guid>https://mariadb.com/kb/en/how-to-configure-columnstore-job-log/+comments/4702</guid></item></channel></rss>